<plot>Made the year after her Oscar nominated triumph - RKO's "Sudden Fear", Joan Crawford was determined to make her MGM comeback armed with a great set of gams, a second-rate script and a few recycled musical numbers including the shockingly-wrong blackface number, "Two-Faced Woman!" The film was a resoundng flop in it's day, but has become among her most beloved cult hits decades later.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?614347</url></doc>
